rComments: Asynchronous class. As long as you watch the lectures and videos given you will easily pass. Tests are easy and clear with the material learned.

Professor Clark-Kazak is brilliant. The class content for ECH2720 is not always the most interesting, but it's not all that bad either. Make sure to follow the criteria on the grading charts and you will have no issue getting an A+ in this class with average effort.

rComments: good teacher, had her for two semesters. very clear expectations for exams, papers based only on class material, quick to answer emails & questions, weekly homework/small assignments for students to keep up with the material. very kind & patient as well, good visual support. 100% best teacher

rComments: Une des meilleures professeures en ECH. Il y a beaucoup de travail a effectuer, mais elle est très claire dans ses attentes et est très compréhensive. Elle nous donne une grille d'évaluation détaillée ainsi que des commentaires pour chacun des travail. Nous étions supposés participé à une simulation, mais ça a été annulé.

She is a good prof, relly often there was misunderstanding between her and srudent. for her if one student understood, everyone else should of as well. She seems to be a quite busy prof and I felt like we were slowing her down in her day. She lost her patience few times but it has to be expected due to her really low tone of voice. Rate A

La moitié de la classe se faisait en ligne et il y avait très peu de participation alors il pouvait être plus difficile de participer dépendamment de la participation de ton groupe. Cette enseignante était toujours disponible et compréhensive tout au long de la session. Très bonne enseignante.

rComments: Bonne enseignante. Elle est toujours disponible à l'extérieur de la classe pour aider. Elle note bien et rapidement les examens. De plus, elle prépare bien ses élèves pour les projets et l'examen final à l'aide de petit quiz tout au long de la session. Je recommande.

She is specialized in research methodology and she knows her stuff. The semester revolves around one project so we get to apply what we see in class to reality, but get ready to work for your grade (but dont get scared shes really nice and comprehensive... Very human)

rComments: The class is quiet straight to the point and half of it was online. To be honest you have to participate if you want a good grade and if you skip a class make sure to have someone for the extra notes. She gives a lecture, but if you want it to be interesting you have to talk. There is papers to read, but no book to buy. And the prof is awesome!!!
